<div id="review_924392755" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/924392755" />
    <a title="ReGina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30079310-regina"><img alt="ReGina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1459025192p2/30079310.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/924392755?book_show_action=true">Apr 29, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="ReGina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="ReGina" href="/user/show/30079310-regina">ReGina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30079310-regina?shelf=beach-books">beach-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30079310-regina?shelf=multi-cultural">multi-cultural</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30079310-regina?shelf=mocha-girls-read-2016-challenge">mocha-girls-read-2016-challenge</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer924392755" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7582475223872083465">This is another book where I wish we had half stars because it is a solid 3.5. Arranged marriages are intriguing to me, and assimilation in all of its many shapes and variations is equally fascinating. Both are front and center in this book. What I also liked about this book is that the point of view is shared between Neel and Leila, and they have solidly contrasting points of view in just about every sense imaginable.<br/><br/>It&apos;s a slow boil, but it really starts to pick up and get interesting. However</span>
  <span id="freeText7582475223872083465" style="display:none">This is another book where I wish we had half stars because it is a solid 3.5. Arranged marriages are intriguing to me, and assimilation in all of its many shapes and variations is equally fascinating. Both are front and center in this book. What I also liked about this book is that the point of view is shared between Neel and Leila, and they have solidly contrasting points of view in just about every sense imaginable.<br /><br />It's a slow boil, but it really starts to pick up and get interesting. However, I would give it 3.5 for the ending, which felt like a quick finish. It's way too neat for the situations that have been presented and it certainly lacks the emotional finish it deserves while it tries to trick you into thinking you've gotten it.<br /><br />I would recommend this book for the theme and POV; just be prepared to be let down when you finish.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7582475223872083465" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


